Earlier this month the Health Ombudsman found that more than 100 patients died under unlawful circumstances. CAPE TOWN President Jacob Zuma has promised that Health Ombudman Malegapuru Makgoba's recommendations regarding the death of the Life Esidimeni psychiatric patients will be implemented.Earlier this month the ombudsman found that more than 100 patients died under unlawful circumstances. Zuma is replying to the two-day debate on the 2017 State of the Nation Address in Parliament this Thursday afternoon. The President says: This matter is deeply painful for the country and should not be used for political gains. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)